WEBVTT

01:16.066 --> 01:16.947
Welcome to Concord.

01:16.967 --> 01:18.971
I don't know about you, but I'm glad to be here.

01:20.413 --> 01:21.354
And I'm Derek.

01:21.555 --> 01:25.581
If I haven't met you yet, I look forward to getting to know you over the next period of time.

01:25.641 --> 01:29.207
And I'm excited to serve as the interim senior pastor here.

01:29.888 --> 01:31.851
God's been at work at Concord for a long time.

01:32.812 --> 01:41.586
And most recently, under the leadership of Pastor Levi, and we're just grateful to God for all that he, God has been doing.

01:41.666 --> 01:49.079
I look forward to serving during this period of time, and then as God brings the next man to lead Concordia Senior Pastor.

01:49.099 --> 01:50.522
So I'm grateful to God to be here.

01:51.624 --> 01:55.030
So on all of our campuses and streaming online, we're glad that you're here.

01:55.651 --> 01:59.057
Whether today's your very first time, or you've been here all your life.

01:59.178 --> 02:00.881
Welcome to Concord, we're glad you're here.

02:01.542 --> 02:06.130
You can go ahead and open your Bibles if you'd like to Joshua chapter one, and we're gonna get there in a moment.

02:07.170 --> 02:22.475
But as we begin today, I'd like to share a couple of things about me and about even the way I approach teaching God's Word that you may already pick up on, but just some things so you can know a little bit more about me and how God's wired me and how I approach life.

02:22.956 --> 02:33.714
In terms of my walk with Christ, a couple of things are really important to me that you'll figure out is, number one, it's profound, but it's simple faith in Jesus.

02:34.050 --> 02:35.793
That, I mean, has changed my life.

02:36.214 --> 02:40.000
I believe that He died for me and rose again and by grace I've been saved through faith.

02:40.581 --> 02:45.449
And so it's not complicated, it's simple, it's powerful, and it's life changing, eternity changing.

02:45.909 --> 02:47.853
And I believe it's available for everyone who will believe.

02:48.754 --> 02:49.816
My God has changed my life.

02:49.836 --> 02:52.380
And so a simple faith in Christ that fuels me.

02:52.821 --> 02:58.450
And it's a deep commitment to just literally reading the Bible and do what it says.

02:58.978 --> 03:01.441
So it's that kind of approach that I have in life.

03:01.862 --> 03:09.431
And I pray that perhaps it's that way for you as well, that you're faith in Christ and then read the Bible and do what it says.

03:09.491 --> 03:16.760
And boy, I know when I can keep those two things right, then everything's right with the way I live my life and follow the Lord.

03:17.100 --> 03:20.344
So that's sort of a little bit about me and just the approach I take in life in general.

03:20.925 --> 03:24.850
And then in terms of teaching God's Word, there's sort of three things I always think about.

03:25.314 --> 03:26.495
And try to describe it this way.

03:27.317 --> 03:34.245
And again, maybe you've already picked up on these or maybe you'll see over, you know, today and the next few weeks and et cetera.

03:35.146 --> 03:43.257
And number one is this, whenever I teach God's Word and preach God's Word, number one, I always say to myself, I want to be biblical, right?

03:44.018 --> 03:49.204
I want you to leave at the end of the message going, that's exactly what the Bible said.

03:49.965 --> 03:53.810
Because I really don't think I can say things anything better than God can.

03:54.562 --> 03:58.890
And so if the message is biblical, then you have heard from the Lord.

03:59.451 --> 04:03.579
So the first place I always start is the message doesn't need to be clever.

04:03.959 --> 04:07.105
It doesn't need to be Derek's opinion, it needs to be.

04:07.205 --> 04:08.828
This is what God's word says.

04:08.929 --> 04:18.386
So I hope that every time you leave, and I pray this will be true of all of our groups, small groups, big groups, all of our meetings, but when we're teaching God's word, it would say,

04:19.234 --> 04:20.416
biblical, so be biblical.

04:20.436 --> 04:22.319
Number two, be relevant.

04:22.339 --> 04:25.084
That's always in my mind, be relevant.

04:25.324 --> 04:32.196
The Bible is not just written to be history book or to tell us how God interacted with people years ago.

04:32.717 --> 04:35.422
The Bible is meant to be relevant to our lives today.

04:35.462 --> 04:41.572
We should be able to read the Bible and go, ah, this is how it should be played out in my life.

04:41.633 --> 04:44.518
This is how I apply the Bible to my daily life.

04:44.538 --> 04:44.818
Now,

04:45.058 --> 04:51.988
I recognize at the end of any Bible study or any message or even when you're just reading the Bible, you have a choice to make.

04:52.830 --> 04:56.155
You may say, this is how God's word applies to my life.

04:56.455 --> 04:58.118
You may choose not to do that.

04:59.560 --> 05:03.005
But at least you've been confronted with, this is how to apply it to my life.

05:03.486 --> 05:11.858
And so my prayer is that at the end of each message you would go, yeah, there's at least one thing that I heard in that message is like, that makes sense in my life.

05:12.098 --> 05:17.204
could apply, and perhaps even if God stirs in your heart, I should apply this to my life.

05:17.564 --> 05:18.686
And then the third one is this.

05:20.267 --> 05:21.008
Don't be boring.

05:22.770 --> 05:26.074
It's a philosophy I have of teaching a Bible and preaching.

05:26.114 --> 05:28.197
Don't be boring.

05:28.657 --> 05:30.639
I don't think God is boring.

05:31.400 --> 05:32.922
I don't think the Bible is boring.

05:33.323 --> 05:37.948
So if the sermon is boring, it's not God's fault.

05:39.109 --> 05:39.730
It's my fault.

05:40.418 --> 05:44.724
If your Bible study is boring, it's not God's fault.

05:46.267 --> 05:49.612
You get to work on how you're presenting the message.

05:49.632 --> 06:01.109
And so my prayer is that you don't come to be entertained, but I pray that in a way that is biblical, relevant, and not boring that God would speak to our hearts each week.

06:01.970 --> 06:03.232
Okay.

06:03.252 --> 06:09.842
Today's text, Joshua chapter one, we're gonna talk about how do you hold on

06:10.146 --> 06:11.988
to God's promises.

06:13.871 --> 06:17.215
God has been working at Concord through the years.

06:17.815 --> 06:29.029
And there's some things He has been doing as a congregation to say, we are trusting in the Lord to help us to expand His kingdom, to pray that He would work in our lives.

06:29.990 --> 06:36.338
Guys, one of the things that I'm praying during this interim period is that each of you would grow spiritually in your faith.

06:36.962 --> 06:42.933
I pray that there will be tremendous growth in your life spiritually, personally, during this next period of time.

06:43.474 --> 06:47.141
I don't sense from anyone that anybody's planning to back up.

06:47.742 --> 06:56.658
Everybody's planning to personally move forward, but also in our church and our ministries, men that we move forward and continue to serve the Lord and then also

06:57.122 --> 07:00.287
on all of our campuses that we would see growth.

07:00.527 --> 07:10.141
I mean, literally more people coming to the churches and to the church as God reaches more people and even through our mission efforts at greater impact around the world.

07:10.782 --> 07:22.680
And so as we see that, we're holding on to God's promises because some people are maybe where the children of Israel will give the context of this passage and then read it.

07:23.381 --> 07:26.546
Maybe you're where the children of Israel were on this day.

07:27.938 --> 07:31.123
They're at the edge of the promised land.

07:31.944 --> 07:36.029
And the promised land represents victorious Christian living.

07:36.771 --> 07:38.152
It's their next step of faith.

07:38.193 --> 07:39.514
It's a big step of faith.

07:40.115 --> 07:46.184
And it's a place of God's blessing, a place of God's just doing amazing work in and through them.

07:46.765 --> 07:48.107
And you're at that kind of a place.

07:49.008 --> 07:53.314
The children of Israel had come out of Egypt through the Red Sea.

07:54.195 --> 07:56.178
Those are some amazing miracles.

07:56.738 --> 08:00.942
Then there had this 40 year wandering in the wilderness.

08:01.823 --> 08:02.744
That was pretty bad.

08:02.764 --> 08:06.888
Although there were some miracles in that as well.

08:07.548 --> 08:08.970
But now they're right on the edge.

08:09.570 --> 08:11.953
And man, God, what are you going to do next?

08:13.795 --> 08:16.717
God's promises, holding on to God's promises.

08:16.757 --> 08:17.979
Let's read Joshua.

08:18.059 --> 08:19.160
Please stay with me, please.

08:19.560 --> 08:25.586
For the reading of God's Word, Joshua chapter one, and I'm going to read verses one through nine.

08:26.594 --> 08:34.523
After the death of Moses, the Lord's servant, the Lord spoke to Joshua, son of none, Moses' assistant.

08:35.765 --> 08:37.447
He said, Moses, my servant is dead.

08:38.208 --> 08:43.954
Now you and all the people prepared to cross over the Jordan to the land I'm given to the Israelites.

08:44.815 --> 08:49.381
I have given you every place where you were the soul of your foot treads.

08:49.921 --> 08:54.066
Just as I promised Moses, your territory will be from the wilderness

08:54.210 --> 09:01.200
11 onto the Great River, the Euphrates River, all the land of the Hittites, and west to the Mediterranean Sea.

09:02.541 --> 09:05.205
No one will be able to stand against you as long as you live.

09:05.786 --> 09:06.527
I will be with you.

09:07.068 --> 09:11.494
Just as I was with Moses, I will not leave you or abandon you.

09:12.275 --> 09:13.697
Be strong and courageous.

09:14.538 --> 09:19.545
For you will distribute the land I swore to their fathers to give them as an inheritance.

09:20.286 --> 09:23.410
Above all, be strong and very courageous.

09:23.874 --> 09:29.241
to observe carefully the whole instruction that my servant Moses commanded you.

09:29.962 --> 09:35.349
Do not turn from it to the right or to the left so that you will have success wherever you go.

09:36.111 --> 09:39.475
This book of instruction must not depart from your mouth.

09:40.036 --> 09:45.623
You are to meditate on it day and night so that you may carefully observe everything written in it.

09:46.605 --> 09:49.288
For then you will prosper and succeed in whatever you do.

09:50.069 --> 09:53.554
Heaven I commanded you be strong and courageous

09:54.146 --> 09:58.553
Do not be afraid or discouraged for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.

09:59.014 --> 09:59.655
Let's pray together.

10:00.837 --> 10:02.199
Thank you Lord for your word.

10:02.239 --> 10:05.705
Thank you Father for speaking to us through your word.

10:06.426 --> 10:10.553
Thank you for your Holy Spirit who helps us to understand the word.

10:10.613 --> 10:15.581
Thank you Father for the Holy Spirit who helps us to understand how to apply your word to our lives.

10:16.262 --> 10:20.850
And so I pray today for each one of us that our prayer would be Lord let me hear your word.

10:21.474 --> 10:24.679
And then we respond with faith and obedience to what you're calling me to do.

10:25.341 --> 10:29.127
Because Father, we don't want to just be here as the Word, but we want to hear it and do what it says.

10:29.688 --> 10:33.334
So Father, lead us all this day in Jesus' name we pray, amen.

10:35.177 --> 10:43.051
So college students, high school students, middle school students, are faced always with choices.

10:43.872 --> 10:47.378
They've got all these friends that are not walking with the Lord, or maybe they've got

10:47.586 --> 10:55.578
classmates, maybe their close friends are walking with the Lord, but they had classmates and there's a lot of pressure around them to not do things God's way.

10:56.680 --> 11:01.267
There's pressure of, you know, language that would not be honored to the Lord.

11:01.788 --> 11:06.435
There's pressure of, I mean, everything from the way you treat people, not in a Godly way.

11:07.197 --> 11:15.890
There's pressure in the classroom to bend the rules, to cheat, to do things that would cause them to get good grades, but not really be honest.

11:17.314 --> 11:24.986
There's relationships and there's pressure in those relationships to do things the world's way rather than the holiness and purity of God's way.

11:25.907 --> 11:41.351
And so the question is, how do we help students to understand, man, when you hold on to God's principles and God's promises, that will lead to life and blessing and success and being right where God wants you to be.

11:43.434 --> 11:45.778
Adults, we have pressure every day.

11:46.370 --> 11:48.592
pressure in relationships, pressure in friendships.

11:49.874 --> 11:51.235
Teenagers, you may not know this.

11:51.275 --> 11:54.559
Peer pressure doesn't stop when you graduate from high school.

11:55.520 --> 11:58.884
I know 70 year old men who still bow to peer pressure all the time.

12:00.405 --> 12:06.212
So how do we make sure all of us, each one of us, that we are holding on to God's promises?

12:07.433 --> 12:09.575
That his way is the right way.

12:09.595 --> 12:11.978
I mean, there may be challenges for you.

12:12.018 --> 12:15.602
The children of Israel had come out of Egypt.

12:16.034 --> 12:24.868
And in Egypt, there was all sorts of ungodliness and worldliness and things that were not honored to God.

12:25.929 --> 12:44.498
And yet God had delivered them from that sinful place, and God had brought them then through the Red Sea, and God had sustained them in the wilderness, and God was about to lead them to a place that they would see His blessings just poured out.

12:45.794 --> 12:52.903
But how do they know they could really believe that everything he said was true and that doing things his way was the right way?

12:53.243 --> 12:55.145
I want to show you four things in this text this morning.

12:55.165 --> 12:57.648
Number one, we're going to hold on to God's promises.

12:58.109 --> 12:59.791
Four things from this text that we need to know.

12:59.831 --> 13:02.414
Number one, the Lord speaks.

13:04.236 --> 13:04.977
God talks.

13:05.918 --> 13:06.719
The Lord speaks.

13:07.420 --> 13:09.403
I like the way that Charles Stanley says it.

13:09.463 --> 13:12.947
The Lord doesn't speak with an audible voice.

13:14.169 --> 13:15.410
He speaks much louder.

13:17.378 --> 13:19.421
He speaks to our heart and to our mind.

13:19.501 --> 13:20.402
God speaks.

13:21.283 --> 13:24.228
The Bible says that the Lord spoke to Moses.

13:24.909 --> 13:31.978
It says, in verse one, after the death of Moses, the Lord's servant, the Lord spoke to Joshua.

13:33.320 --> 13:43.214
And later he says that just as I was with Moses and just as I promised Moses, the Lord spoke to Moses and we know some pretty amazing ways, right?

13:43.955 --> 13:45.938
I mean, the Lord spoke to Moses

13:46.466 --> 13:48.128
through a burning bush.

13:49.410 --> 13:52.895
I don't know about you, but the Lord has never spoken to me through a burning bush.

13:54.398 --> 14:11.002
I heard one guy say that, you know, in our day and age, if the Lord spoke to anybody through a burning bush, the problem with that in our day and age would be somebody then would figure a way to put that in a box and sell it.

14:11.983 --> 14:13.906
Either at a store on TV,

14:14.114 --> 14:17.097
And they would say, here's God in a box in a burning bush.

14:17.738 --> 14:19.179
And they would try to sell that to you.

14:20.140 --> 14:30.111
God spoke in that very unique way to get Moses' attention because he had a specific thing he wanted to do, but Moses knew it was God, and God spoke to him in that way.

14:30.712 --> 14:34.216
God spoke to him on the mountain, right?

14:34.396 --> 14:39.261
On Mount Sinai, when God spoke and said, here's the law, the 10 commandments and the whole law.

14:39.701 --> 14:43.986
And God spoke clearly, and he spoke to Moses, and Moses knew what he said, and it was the,

14:44.130 --> 14:48.616
kinds of things that everybody resume with says, yes, this is the word of the Lord.

14:49.818 --> 14:54.183
But God spoke to Moses in his heart and his mind, and God spoke to Moses.

14:54.264 --> 14:55.545
Nobody questioned that, right?

14:56.326 --> 15:01.713
The problem for the Israelites on this day, the day we're talking about in our taxes, Moses has died.

15:02.675 --> 15:07.501
And so they had a bit of a crisis of belief.

15:08.062 --> 15:10.245
Could God speak to anybody else?

15:11.386 --> 15:14.130
Now we, through the lens of Jesus,

15:14.338 --> 15:15.499
death and resurrection.

15:15.840 --> 15:25.672
We through the recorded Word of God, having the 66 books written down, we can look back and go, well, of course God was going to continue to speak.

15:26.293 --> 15:28.296
But on that day, they weren't really sure.

15:28.356 --> 15:38.389
And Joshua who had this mentor Moses, this leader, how could he know that God was going to continue to speak?

15:38.409 --> 15:42.674
But the Lord spoke to Moses and the Lord spoke to Joshua.

15:43.170 --> 15:48.017
And he continued in this passage, we see some of the things that he said to Joshua.

15:48.578 --> 15:51.863
But let me ask you, do you believe that God spoke to Moses?

15:52.023 --> 15:52.464
Yes or no?

15:52.985 --> 15:53.245
Yes.

15:54.167 --> 15:55.609
Did God speak to Joshua?

15:55.849 --> 15:56.110
Yes.

15:56.831 --> 15:58.093
Does God speak to us today?

15:58.133 --> 15:58.794
Yes.

16:00.076 --> 16:04.562
God speaks, I love the way that Dr. Blackaby says it in Experiencing God, Bible study.

16:05.464 --> 16:10.231
In book, he says, God speaks most regularly by the Holy Spirit in four specific ways.

16:10.291 --> 16:12.274
And one of those is through the Bible.

16:12.674 --> 16:16.419
So you asked, how does God speak to me today?

16:17.761 --> 16:19.523
God speaks through His Word.

16:19.944 --> 16:25.151
So every time you read God's Word, I've got good news to you.

16:25.912 --> 16:28.355
God is speaking directly to you.

16:29.737 --> 16:37.668
And so I ask you, right off the bat, you know, where are you in terms of your relationship to the Bible?

16:38.248 --> 16:42.514
In other words, do you have the daily discipline, a habit of reading God's Word?

16:43.842 --> 16:49.130
I was talking to a young man a while ago, and he was going through a very difficult time.

16:49.210 --> 16:53.557
His father had done some illegal activities, and so his father was in prison.

16:54.098 --> 17:03.633
This kid was at a crisis of faith, trying to figure out, he didn't even really know if he knew God, didn't know if he knew Jesus as his personal Lord and Savior.

17:03.954 --> 17:11.826
I shared the gospel with him, and I also shared with him, I said, listen, you really need to read the Bible.

17:12.514 --> 17:13.695
And to pray.

17:13.755 --> 17:15.117
And so I actually encouraged him.

17:15.137 --> 17:18.581
He had not read the Bible ever in his life.

17:18.701 --> 17:23.026
He had gone to church, but had never like literally just picked up his Bible at home and just read it.

17:23.526 --> 17:27.771
And I said, I challenge you just to take a little bit and read the Gospel of John.

17:27.791 --> 17:28.992
That's why I encourage him to start.

17:30.334 --> 17:34.058
So the next time we got back together, just a few weeks later, I said, hey, how's everything going?

17:34.078 --> 17:35.820
I mean, his dad was still in prison.

17:35.840 --> 17:36.921
And so that was difficult.

17:37.502 --> 17:41.426
And I said, well, what has God been saying to you through his word?

17:42.242 --> 17:43.344
What has God been saying to you?

17:43.364 --> 17:44.626
I think that's the way I ask the question.

17:45.126 --> 17:47.710
And he says, well, I really haven't been getting the answers.

17:48.491 --> 17:49.352
And I said, really?

17:50.054 --> 17:51.836
And he said, well, I've been praying.

17:51.856 --> 17:53.999
And I said, okay.

17:54.841 --> 17:56.924
I said, well, but you've been reading the Bible?

17:56.984 --> 18:01.410
He goes, no, I haven't been reading the Bible because I wanted God to speak directly to me.

18:02.952 --> 18:12.146
And I said, I want you to see, when you read the Bible, God is speaking directly to you.

18:12.578 --> 18:13.939
So many people miss that.

18:14.680 --> 18:20.105
They think they're looking for God in a cloud, right?

18:20.125 --> 18:28.574
They're looking for images of God or they're looking for an answer on a billboard or they're looking for an answer in some other thing.

18:28.594 --> 18:32.378
I mean, are they going to see an image on a tree or something like that?

18:32.398 --> 18:40.786
I mean, it's some crazy stuff sometimes people look for and God has so clearly written his word down for us to read.

18:40.866 --> 18:42.428
I don't know what your pattern is.

18:43.029 --> 18:50.198
A long time ago, the Lord convicted me that for my discipline and my walk with God, I needed to read through the Bible every year.

18:51.019 --> 18:53.623
And so I have a regular pattern of reading through the Bible.

18:53.643 --> 18:58.489
So it's a couple of chapters, three chapters a day about and to read through the Bible every year.

18:58.509 --> 19:02.034
That keeps me grounded and focused and moving forward in my faith.

19:02.855 --> 19:03.736
I don't know what yours is.

19:03.876 --> 19:08.562
Maybe you read a verse a day or a chapter a day or a few verses a day.

19:08.962 --> 19:17.572
Warren Wiersby says it this way, he says, if you want answers, the way you're gonna get the answers right on time is through the regular reading of God's Word.

19:18.633 --> 19:26.902
And so I just challenge you, this may be the way of just applying this message to your life, you may say, I need to begin daily to read God's Word.

19:27.362 --> 19:35.852
Because if you're gonna hold on to God's promises, you've got to know what they are and the Lord needs to speak to you and the Lord wants to speak to you and He will speak to you through His Word.

19:36.513 --> 19:37.714
On the YouVersion app,

19:38.370 --> 19:42.994
The Bible app and so many other apps, there are things that you're gonna get.

19:43.195 --> 19:49.020
And so whether you're reading on a paper Bible, reading on your phone, reading God's Word, put God's Word in your heart.

19:50.041 --> 19:50.361
Got it?

19:50.421 --> 19:54.765
We need to allow God to speak to us, buy the Holy Spirit through the Bible.

19:55.086 --> 19:56.567
God also does speak through prayer.

19:56.907 --> 19:59.510
That's the second way God speaks to us very regularly.

19:59.790 --> 20:01.252
God does speak to you through prayer.

20:01.652 --> 20:08.178
And so as you talk to God and you listen to God, God speaks

20:08.482 --> 20:16.612
But one of the things that you can know, God will always speak through prayer in line with his word.

20:17.693 --> 20:23.580
God will never say something to you in prayer that he will conflict with his word.

20:23.961 --> 20:30.008
So if you ever come to me or any of your Bible say leaders in the pastors and go, God told me to do something.

20:30.048 --> 20:34.433
And it's like illegal and moral, ungodly, unbiblical.

20:35.054 --> 20:36.536
And you say, God told me to do that.

20:36.696 --> 20:38.258
I'm going to say, no, he didn't.

20:39.458 --> 20:40.920
And I'm going to stand on God's word.

20:41.841 --> 20:46.526
And so we say, God, I want you to speak to me in my heart through prayer.

20:47.447 --> 20:50.912
And that was what that young man was looking for on that day when I was talking to him.

20:51.232 --> 20:58.080
But that young man need to start with a daily dose of God's word so that even his prayers were transformed by the Word of God.

20:58.601 --> 21:00.283
God speaks through the Bible, through prayer.

21:00.623 --> 21:03.186
God also speaks through other believers.

21:03.554 --> 21:19.673
when we're in a Bible study setting or a sermon or even a conversation with another believer, somebody who you're talking with may just say a word and they don't even know that they're giving you just a word from God's word that is really helpful for you to hold on to.

21:19.793 --> 21:22.516
I mean, maybe you don't even say about a decision you're gonna make.

21:22.557 --> 21:28.203
Maybe you're just talking about something and they say something or maybe you do say, I've got a decision to make.

21:28.644 --> 21:30.546
What do you see in God's word?

21:30.914 --> 21:31.916
that would help guide me.

21:32.236 --> 21:35.262
And they speak that word from God's word from the Bible.

21:35.802 --> 21:37.886
And it gives you guidance and direction.

21:38.728 --> 21:54.515
It's why one of the reasons we say, a firm what the Bible says, it talks about where two or three are gathered, that their God is in the midst of them because the Bible says by the testimony of two or three witnesses, a manner shall be established.

21:54.535 --> 21:56.338
What that practically means is,

21:56.546 --> 22:08.744
You've got godly people together, whether in a grow group or community group, any kind of small group, an accountability group of friends, you can help to see God's word clearly to get guidance on your decisions.

22:09.064 --> 22:15.073
So the Lord speaks by the Holy Spirit through the Bible, through prayer, through believers, and through circumstances.

22:15.754 --> 22:17.616
God can speak through circumstances.

22:18.077 --> 22:21.522
But again, those are always in line with His word.

22:22.402 --> 22:27.228
And he's going to confirm them in so many ways through prayer, through other believers.

22:27.789 --> 22:49.879
One example for my life, I don't have time to tell the whole story today, but when I was 17 years old, it was quite a few years ago, 31 years ago, during the summer, I had very simple arthroscopic surgery on my knee, had some knee cartilage issues, and it was just to clean out the cartilage so I could get back to football and basketball and baseball and keep playing.

22:49.899 --> 22:52.402
But through that surgery somehow,

22:52.834 --> 22:57.500
I was contracted a staff infection.

22:58.121 --> 22:59.482
And it was localized on my knee.

23:00.604 --> 23:01.505
Nasty, nasty.

23:01.785 --> 23:09.095
Put me back in the hospital three weeks, three surgeries later, 30 pounds lighter.

23:09.235 --> 23:10.536
I finally got out of the hospital.

23:11.077 --> 23:12.178
I looked awful.

23:12.619 --> 23:15.803
And I asked my parents, they were with me in the hospital for 24-7.

23:15.903 --> 23:17.385
One of them was always there.

23:17.405 --> 23:19.868
I asked my parents later, I'm like, did y'all think I was going to die?

23:20.749 --> 23:21.330
And they said,

23:21.666 --> 23:24.709
I actually know that doctors never thought you were going to die.

23:24.729 --> 23:31.857
He said, but if the third surgery wouldn't have worked to get the infection out, they were going to have to remove your leg.

23:32.077 --> 23:33.018
You're about to lose your leg.

23:33.739 --> 23:35.221
I didn't realize it was that serious.

23:35.301 --> 23:38.424
It was really, really serious.

23:38.444 --> 23:48.535
But that circumstance, God used to speak to me in line with His word, and I'll tell you more about it later, to get me where He wanted me to be.

23:48.595 --> 23:51.538
That's an example of a

23:51.650 --> 23:53.532
That's sort of an extreme circumstance.

23:54.153 --> 23:58.639
But through the big and the small circumstances of life, God can't speak to us.

23:59.180 --> 24:01.522
But again, He always speaks in line with His word.

24:01.923 --> 24:02.784
So the Lord speaks.

24:02.824 --> 24:08.852
If we're going to hold on to God's promises, we must see that the Lord speaks and He speaks to us even today.

24:08.892 --> 24:09.793
That's the point.

24:10.514 --> 24:14.499
Number two, not only does the Lord speak, but the Lord makes bold promises.

24:15.260 --> 24:20.146
For the children of Israel, some of the promises were grounded in their history.

24:20.418 --> 24:25.587
The promise of, I've taken you and brought you out of Egypt through the Red Sea.

24:26.488 --> 24:28.451
I've sustained you in the promised land.

24:28.992 --> 24:33.259
I mean, I'm sorry, I've sustained you in the wilderness to get you to the promised land.

24:34.461 --> 24:38.108
These bold promises, it was bold when he says I'm gonna get you out of Egypt.

24:38.709 --> 24:42.855
Only God could have done that and through the power displayed in the plagues he did.

24:43.597 --> 24:46.802
It was a bold promise to say, I'm gonna get you across the Red Sea.

24:46.882 --> 24:51.488
and splitting the waters only as God could have done, He got them across the Red Sea.

24:52.550 --> 24:59.178
In the wilderness, let me give you three words to think about about how bold God's promises were.

24:59.198 --> 25:00.941
He promised them provision.

25:01.882 --> 25:03.885
In the wilderness, how are you going to feed all those people?

25:04.125 --> 25:08.251
There's not a McDonald's or a Subway or a grocery store on every corner in the wilderness.

25:09.052 --> 25:12.716
God provided the food they needed, the water they needed to sustain them.

25:14.038 --> 25:16.882
God provided even for things like

25:17.474 --> 25:21.979
Their shoes did not wear out all those years of wandering the wilderness.

25:21.999 --> 25:25.403
That was a miracle of God's provision and his sustaining.

25:26.485 --> 25:31.190
He even provided, I've been to Israel and actually been to Northern Egypt as well.

25:31.250 --> 25:36.997
And in Israel, there's actually this green plant that still grows to this day.

25:37.638 --> 25:44.626
And this green plant, you take it on your hand and it's basically natural growing hand sanitizer.

25:45.058 --> 25:47.220
It still grows there to this day.

25:47.660 --> 25:52.345
And that would have been what they used to make sure they had cleanliness in the wilderness.

25:52.505 --> 25:55.408
Pretty amazing stuff the way God provides.

25:55.848 --> 26:01.394
And then also not only has God promised provision, but he promises protection.

26:02.114 --> 26:03.195
He promises protection.

26:03.456 --> 26:06.919
He promises them that he's going to protect them from their enemies in the future.

26:07.640 --> 26:10.302
Just like he had protected them from the Egyptians.

26:10.703 --> 26:14.226
Just how he had protected them in the wilderness with all of these

26:14.562 --> 26:17.286
Nations that could have come against them in the wilderness.

26:17.607 --> 26:24.897
The nations stayed away because of the reputation of the Lord and what He had done in Egypt and through them.

26:25.578 --> 26:27.000
God protect them from their enemies.

26:27.020 --> 26:30.125
But here's something I want us to see this true for us today.

26:30.666 --> 26:36.294
Some of the enemies that they faced then are the same enemies we face now.

26:38.017 --> 26:39.459
Their enemies like fear.

26:40.761 --> 26:42.583
Their enemies like temptation.

26:43.425 --> 26:44.306
Their enemies like

26:44.386 --> 26:44.967
guilt.

26:45.808 --> 26:48.692
They're enemies like getting stuck in regret.

26:49.092 --> 27:01.089
Enemies like bitterness and unforgiveness and all these enemies that try to come against us, God gave them victory and He promised to give them victory and He will give you victory over them as well based in His Word.

27:01.109 --> 27:08.619
These guys could have been afraid of their enemies, the Hittites and others that are mentioned here, but God was protecting them from their enemies.

27:08.939 --> 27:13.906
And the Lord made a bold promise not only for provision and protection, but also

27:13.986 --> 27:14.927
the promised land.

27:15.588 --> 27:18.452
And the promised land was a land flow with milk and honey.

27:18.973 --> 27:25.562
If you've been to Israel, boy, you know, like you can drop a seed in some parts of it and they just poom grows.

27:26.243 --> 27:32.792
I mean, just pretty amazing, especially in the northern, the Galilee region, just amazing the way things grow there.

27:33.673 --> 27:35.696
God, though, it's not just about the food.

27:36.157 --> 27:39.742
This promised land represented victorious Christian living.

27:40.042 --> 27:42.866
What Jesus says when he says, I've come that you may have life,

27:43.138 --> 27:44.260
And have it abundantly.

27:44.721 --> 27:46.443
This is what God gives us in Christ.

27:46.824 --> 27:49.729
And God promises that He will give us that.

27:50.230 --> 27:54.076
There's a victorious Christian living and we can stand on His promises.

27:54.436 --> 27:57.501
So the Lord speaks, He makes these bold promises.

27:57.962 --> 28:00.667
Thirdly, I want to see that the Lord keeps His word.

28:01.207 --> 28:10.162
There's four phrases I want you to see in this text that are very clear to the Israelites and are powerful for us today as well.

28:10.242 --> 28:11.844
The first one is this, this phrase.

28:11.864 --> 28:18.113
The Lord keeps his word, he says in verse number five, I will be with you.

28:20.857 --> 28:21.578
I'll be with you.

28:24.462 --> 28:25.203
I'll be with you.

28:26.164 --> 28:28.387
You go through a difficult time, the Lord is with you.

28:29.849 --> 28:33.935
Your children, your grandchildren, they do things that are painful.

28:34.335 --> 28:37.880
They're painful for you as a parent and a grandkid and as a grandparent.

28:38.160 --> 28:39.282
And you begin to think, Lord,

28:39.458 --> 28:40.159
Where are you?

28:40.719 --> 28:42.241
And the Lord says, I'm with you.

28:43.442 --> 28:43.963
I'm with you.

28:44.524 --> 28:53.934
Jesus says in the Great Commission, as you go to make disciples of all nations, I will be with you to the very end of the age.

28:54.415 --> 29:06.048
So as you advance God's kingdom, as you live for Christ at school and on your job and in your home and everywhere you go, the Lord is with you.

29:06.668 --> 29:08.050
So the Lord speaks

29:08.386 --> 29:12.870
He makes bold promises, provision, protection, victorious Christian living.

29:12.890 --> 29:16.454
And he says, listen, I'm not just promising you that and go do it on your own.

29:16.554 --> 29:19.156
He says, I am with you.

29:19.637 --> 29:28.705
When Christ became your Lord and savior, the Holy Spirit became living inside of you and the Lord is with you everywhere that you go.

29:29.106 --> 29:31.168
The Lord says, I will be with you.

29:31.428 --> 29:32.589
But not only I'll be with you.

29:32.649 --> 29:38.034
He says, takes a step further and says, I will not leave you or forsake you.

29:38.562 --> 29:40.904
In verse number five, he says, I will never leave you.

29:41.265 --> 29:43.467
I will not leave you or abandon you.

29:43.787 --> 29:45.709
I will not leave you or forsake you.

29:46.389 --> 29:52.635
Again, sometimes when you go through health challenges or financial crisis, it begins to feel like, God, you're so far away.

29:52.675 --> 29:55.678
Have you left me and the Lord says, no, I haven't left you.

29:56.078 --> 29:56.759
I am with you.

29:57.960 --> 29:58.781
I am with you.

29:59.061 --> 30:01.223
The Lord says, I will be with you.

30:01.724 --> 30:03.646
I will not leave you or forsake you.

30:03.686 --> 30:04.727
The Lord keeps his word.

30:05.207 --> 30:08.370
He also says, I will show you

30:08.546 --> 30:08.986
the way.

30:10.168 --> 30:10.988
I will show you the way.

30:11.629 --> 30:13.210
He tells them where they're to go.

30:13.250 --> 30:18.495
He talks about going from the wilderness to Lebanon.

30:18.515 --> 30:24.161
This is verse number four to the Great River, Euphrates, all the way to the Mediterranean Sea.

30:24.201 --> 30:25.942
The Lord says, I will show you the way.

30:26.082 --> 30:27.824
I won't show you where to live, I'll show you where to go.

30:28.985 --> 30:35.331
And so for us as followers of Jesus, he's not talking about geographic land, although sometimes he does, right?

30:36.192 --> 30:38.514
We actually understand this when we think about

30:38.818 --> 30:43.404
Missionaries that they need to move from this location to the other parts of the world.

30:43.905 --> 30:47.490
But do you know God doesn't just speak to pastors and missionaries that way?

30:48.151 --> 30:51.595
God may speak to you and say, I want you to move to a new job.

30:52.396 --> 30:54.419
I want you to move to a new community.

30:55.400 --> 31:04.933
I want you to, so it can be geographic, but it's also, hey, on your daily, in your daily life, everywhere that you go, I will show you the way.

31:05.634 --> 31:08.338
And so a simple prayer would be, Lord, lead and guide me today.

31:08.770 --> 31:09.932
Show me where you want to go.

31:10.653 --> 31:12.275
If I'm at the grocery store, I'll live for you.

31:12.676 --> 31:14.899
If I'm at work, I'm at school, I'm at my home.

31:15.840 --> 31:28.097
You will show me the way, but it's not only show me the way of where to go, but it's show me the way of how to live there and how to follow Jesus and how to respond with each situation.

31:29.760 --> 31:30.581
I'll give you an example.

31:30.941 --> 31:32.844
Maybe you're reading through Romans chapter 12.

31:33.725 --> 31:35.448
And you say, you know what?

31:35.468 --> 31:37.010
I've got somebody that hurt me.

31:37.218 --> 31:39.840
And my natural reaction is to get them back.

31:40.841 --> 31:42.823
Or like some people say, I don't get even.

31:43.784 --> 31:44.785
I get ahead, right?

31:44.905 --> 31:45.946
You know people that say it that way?

31:47.488 --> 31:51.692
But the way of Christ says, I'm not going to do it that way.

31:52.112 --> 31:55.295
If somebody offends me, I'm going to give it to the Lord.

31:56.056 --> 31:59.859
Because the Lord says in Romans 12, do not seek revenge.

32:00.400 --> 32:02.281
Do not seek to pay back.

32:02.301 --> 32:04.383
Leave room for God in his wrath.

32:04.804 --> 32:07.186
Because vengeance his mind says to the Lord.

32:08.482 --> 32:13.229
So Romans 12 would guide us on showing us the way to respond to that situation.

32:13.650 --> 32:15.653
That's an example of what we're talking about here.

32:16.274 --> 32:17.376
God will show us the way.

32:17.716 --> 32:20.501
And then fourthly, the Lord keeps his word.

32:20.881 --> 32:22.203
He says, I will be with you.

32:22.223 --> 32:23.425
I will not leave you for sake.

32:23.525 --> 32:24.247
I will show you the way.

32:24.607 --> 32:27.011
And fourthly, he says, I will fight your battles.

32:28.193 --> 32:29.194
I will fight your battles.

32:30.276 --> 32:32.800
I don't know what battles you're going to face this week.

32:32.820 --> 32:36.786
I mean, maybe physical challenges, spiritual battles, financial challenges,

32:37.474 --> 32:40.157
The Lord says, I will fight your battles.

32:40.418 --> 32:42.660
That's what he says about them with the Hittites.

32:43.221 --> 32:47.386
He says in verse six, I will give you as an inheritance.

32:47.827 --> 32:50.049
The Lord is the one that's gonna fight the battles.

32:50.470 --> 32:52.572
And in verse seven, he talks about this.

32:53.133 --> 32:57.218
Where you go to the right to the left, I will give you success wherever you go.

32:57.258 --> 33:00.122
The Lord is the one to fight your battles.

33:00.642 --> 33:01.503
Because let's think about it.

33:01.864 --> 33:03.706
Here's a couple ways you could approach challenges.

33:03.986 --> 33:07.090
One you could say, God, there's these challenges before me.

33:07.426 --> 33:09.249
I'm gonna really do my best.

33:09.970 --> 33:12.574
And God, I'll let you know how it goes.

33:13.315 --> 33:15.078
And you just try with all your strength.

33:15.098 --> 33:17.902
Maybe there's somebody in your family that's really not loving.

33:17.922 --> 33:19.725
It's hard to love them.

33:20.265 --> 33:27.276
You could try with all your strength just to be very loving and you're gonna get worn out over time.

33:28.578 --> 33:32.063
Or you can say, God, you have loved me so much.

33:32.924 --> 33:34.146
You love me in Christ.

33:34.927 --> 33:36.690
You put your Holy Spirit in with me.

33:37.026 --> 33:38.469
You love me so much.

33:39.030 --> 33:42.235
God, may I be an overflow of your love.

33:42.656 --> 33:48.807
God, strengthen me and fill me and help me to see you loving people through me.

33:49.628 --> 33:54.096
God's supply is unending and he will fight our battles.

33:54.497 --> 33:55.318
He will be the one.

33:55.959 --> 34:00.167
These are battles that affect our heart, our mind, these battles that we talked about.

34:00.768 --> 34:02.130
I'll encourage you in this.

34:02.466 --> 34:08.732
If you read through the book of songs and you see all the battles that David was fighting, it wasn't just the physical enemies.

34:09.533 --> 34:10.474
It wasn't just people.

34:11.134 --> 34:16.620
David was fighting the things we're talking about, the guilt, the fear, all these kinds of things, the unloving.

34:17.060 --> 34:18.121
David was fighting these.

34:18.341 --> 34:19.602
The Lord keeps his word.

34:19.863 --> 34:20.704
I will fight your battles.

34:21.064 --> 34:23.867
And then fourthly, the Lord tells us how to respond.

34:24.908 --> 34:26.029
He tells us how to respond.

34:26.429 --> 34:29.212
In verses six through nine, he says over and over.

34:29.492 --> 34:31.634
Verse six, be strong and courageous.

34:32.130 --> 34:34.894
Verse seven, be strong and very courageous.

34:35.915 --> 34:38.219
And in verse nine, he says, haven't I commanded you?

34:38.499 --> 34:40.622
Be strong and courageous.

34:40.642 --> 34:42.344
You know why he kept telling Joshua that?

34:43.506 --> 34:47.792
Because Joshua wasn't feeling very strong or courageous at all.

34:48.753 --> 34:50.035
And God knew that.

34:50.997 --> 34:53.720
Joshua needed a reminder and we do too.

34:54.061 --> 35:00.530
Be strong and courageous, but not just again in our own strength, but we draw from the strength of the Lord.

35:01.090 --> 35:03.213
And we say, God, you be my strength.

35:03.573 --> 35:04.614
You give me courage.

35:05.536 --> 35:06.737
Be strong and courageous.

35:07.138 --> 35:13.726
And then secondly, the Lord tells us how to respond by living according to God's word.

35:14.387 --> 35:20.194
Verse eight, this book of instruction must not depart from your mouth.

35:21.075 --> 35:29.906
You are to meditate on it day and night so that you may carefully observe everything written in it.

35:30.594 --> 35:36.202
You know what folks, it's gonna take me a lifetime to figure out how to obey everything written in this word.

35:38.946 --> 35:43.553
But boy, it's a great challenge and a great privilege every day.

35:44.695 --> 35:47.639
You may say, Derek, I don't really have a lot of time.

35:48.380 --> 35:50.964
I don't have time to read the Bible and really think about it.

35:51.785 --> 35:53.007
One pastor said it this way.

35:53.909 --> 36:00.338
When you think about Facebook and Twitter, YouTube, Instagram,

36:00.706 --> 36:04.870
Snapchat or your other favorite social media platforms.

36:05.471 --> 36:06.632
Here's the way the pastor said it.

36:07.573 --> 36:14.639
If social media teaches us anything, it teaches us we can't stand before God and say, God, I didn't have time to read the Bible.

36:17.362 --> 36:21.165
And if we read the word, then we respond by doing what it says.

36:21.966 --> 36:28.352
My prayer for all of us is that we will live our lives in accordance to God's Word.

36:28.372 --> 36:30.194
So I don't know about you, how you need to respond.

36:31.138 --> 36:36.786
Perhaps you need to make a fresh and a new commitment to read God's word and to live by it.

36:37.728 --> 36:42.395
Maybe for some though, you say, I don't really have any desire to do that.

36:42.415 --> 36:45.680
I would ask you, do you know Jesus as your Lord and savior?

36:46.501 --> 36:51.108
Because if he is your Lord and savior, he'll give you a desire to read and to live by his word.

36:51.749 --> 36:56.316
And so today, perhaps today for some of you needs to be the day of your salvation.

36:56.676 --> 37:00.562
Would you bow with me in prayer as we close out this service in just a few minutes?

37:01.474 --> 37:09.022
With heads bowed and eyes closed, I ask you, first of all, is Jesus the Lord and Savior of your life?

37:14.247 --> 37:20.294
If he's not yet, then today we want to show you how that he can be your Lord and your Savior.

37:21.755 --> 37:28.402
But secondly, I ask you, is your life committed to God's Word

37:28.994 --> 37:31.337
Are you holding on to God's promises?

37:32.698 --> 37:43.109
I don't know the situation you're going through, but God does, and he cares, and we care, and we want you to rest in his promises.

37:43.570 --> 37:46.113
Trust in him and trust in his word.

37:46.914 --> 37:50.598
So will you afresh in a new commit to God's word?

37:53.501 --> 37:58.386
And again, today, if you need to receive Christ, will you receive Jesus?

37:58.690 --> 38:00.933
as the Lord and Savior of your life.

38:03.756 --> 38:05.478
Now here in this place, let me ask you.

38:07.640 --> 38:11.184
Whether you're in this place, watching online one of our campuses even.

38:12.165 --> 38:14.368
And you need to trust Jesus as your Lord and Savior.

38:15.249 --> 38:18.733
Would you right now say, I'll do that.

38:20.295 --> 38:21.676
I wanna do that, I need to do that.

38:23.639 --> 38:26.642
If that's you, then in just a moment when we stand,

38:28.162 --> 38:33.029
And we begin to sing, would you just come to me at one of our other pastors and say, today, I need to give my life to Christ.

38:34.671 --> 38:39.999
Others of you, you may need to come and say, I need to be baptized very soon.

38:41.061 --> 38:46.148
Others may say, I am ready to make Concord my church home.

38:47.951 --> 38:53.138
We invite you to come for any of those reasons, salvation, baptism to join this church.

38:54.306 --> 39:11.222
There may be others who need to make a commitment from where you're seated or even come and pray at the front here and say, I'm gonna make a commitment of fresh and anew to reading God's Word and to living my life by God's Word because His Word is our foundation.

39:13.284 --> 39:14.966
So I'm gonna pray and we're gonna stand.

39:15.186 --> 39:16.647
You respond how you're leading.

39:16.667 --> 39:17.848
God's leading you to respond today.

39:18.549 --> 39:20.351
Lord Jesus, we thank You for Your Word.

39:21.231 --> 39:23.954
We want to always hold on to Your promises.

39:24.450 --> 39:28.836
And we pray Father that you'd help each one of us to respond the way your leadness to respond today.

39:29.417 --> 39:34.224
For salvation, baptism, church membership, or in other ways.

39:34.905 --> 39:35.405
We love you.

39:35.986 --> 39:38.770
Help us each now to be obedient to what you're calling us to do.

39:38.810 --> 39:39.892
In Jesus' name we pray.

39:40.452 --> 39:40.773
Amen.

39:41.053 --> 39:42.936
Please stand if God's leading you to come.

39:42.996 --> 39:44.498
You respond as He's leading you.

